/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/brahtopg_p5_25_124/rounds/round_1/merge_prompt.md:32:    "claim": "The zapper lets each caller choose both `allowanceTarget` and `swapTarget`, then grants `inputToken` allowance before making an arbitrary external call. Because the approved spender does not have to be the contract that is actually called, a user can intentionally leave a live allowance to a malicious spender and later use that allowance to pull any same-token balance that becomes stranded in the zapper.",
